Inscription east facing of Dharmadhātu Maṇḍala

W: 26.4, H: 4

1. saṃvat 954 māgha śudi 2 thva kunhu pau-
  2. kolāchi vantāo pitāmahapiṃ-
  3. sya dvayakā taogu phalecā ji-
  4. rṇaoddhāra yāṅā devisaṃṣa thakā-
  5. ḍi prabhittisana varṇa siṃ dhanaguṃ-
  6. dha viṣṇumāna siṃ pāhā siṃ
  7. puna siṃ _ _ va narasiṃ che narasiṃ
  8. teja agni siṃ thvate samu(ha) jusya pha-
  9. lecā lhonāva palidāna biyā
  10. juro śubhaṃ ||

 

Provisional Translation:

On the 2nd day of the bright half of the lunar month of Māgha in NS 950 (1830 CE), the phalcā built by the grandfathers in the eastern part of Paukolachi (the older name of Bhindyaḥlachi) has been renovated and offered the roof by Devisaṃṣa, the senior most (thakāḍī) and other persons of the group such as Varṇa Siṃ, Dhanaguṃdha, Viṣṇumāna Siṃ, Pāhā Siṃ, Pun Siṃ, _ _va Narasiṃ, Che Narasiṃ, Teja Agni Siṃ. May there be auspiciousness.

 

[1] The older name of Bhindyaḥlachi.

historical event transliteration and tra:
Summary of the inscription

On the bright fortnight of Śrāvaṇa in NS 991 (1871 CE), a monastery (vihāra) called Triratna was constructed together with a rest house (phalcā) in front of the caitya located at Saptapurī Mahāvihāra, and a statue of triple gems (triratna) was established there on the same day. Triratna Vihāra was constructed by a family (consisting of older brother Bhānuvīra, younger brother Mānavīra and Siddhimāna, and sons and daughters) after having performed worships at all the monasteries of Lalitapura. Further, they donated certain plots of land in different places in order to please Triratna Buddha. It is instructed that the yearly income from the land should be spent on the activities that take place in the monastery.

historical event transliteration and tra:
१. स्वस्ति   ।।   श्रीश्रीजययोगनरेन्द्रमल्लदेव   श्रीश्रीजयभूपालेन्द्रमल्लदेव   श्रीश्रीजयभूपतीन्द्रमल्लदेव स्वम्ह राजान नेपालस 

   अनीति जुओ सोयाओ राजा राजाया जीवउपरस सङाओ 

२. उलिया निमित्तन श्री ३ तलेजुमाजुस्के सिजलपति तास्यं तया भाखा, कंतुया बबु महादेव उझान अनेक ककतक विद्यदान 

   बियाओ फुतकु, विनाअपराधस एल छोङाओ कुतका–ओ

३. फुतकु, भीममल्लया खं मयासिंङ कङाओ श्रीभिममल्ल फुतकु, अनेक राजा राजा फाओ, अनेक स्वेष्ठ फुतकु, अनेक देवताया 

   मन्त्र सेनकु, बालस्त्री मैथुन याङाओ स्याक, थथिङ महादेव उ–

४. झाया काय कंतु उझा, थ्व ङ्हपां वदल उझाया सेवा याङाओ चोङ, ओलस बदल उझा जयकृष्णजु व निम्हसेन मान्धातायाके 

   सेवां यातुक, मान्धाता मखुथे थुयकाओ, जयकृष्णजु नेम्ह

५. बाकाय स्याक, ध्वजराज स्याक, बदल उझा पितिङछोक, थ्वनंलि ओझा हेयकाओ थमं ङ्हलुयाओ मान्धाता स्यायतङ, उगुलि 

   सियाओ, मान्धातान कंतु पितिनछोक, थुगुलि खुनसन चि–

६. कुतिओ मिलय याङाओ मान्धाता स्याक, ओलसं हनकं चिकुतिया उपरस सङ, श्रीश्रीनृपेन्द्रमल्ल जुजुन पितिङछोक, ओलसं 

   हानकनं चिकुतिन बोङाओ तओ हानकनं चिकुतिया उपरस सङओ ।

७. चिकुति बीयकर छोक, ओनलि श्रीश्रीपार्थिवेन्द्रमल्ल श्रीश्रीभूपतीन्द्रमल्ल नेम्ह फाव, वंशीधर बाओत किसि थुमिस जीवया उपरस

   सङ, थ्वगुलि सियाओ श्रीश्रीजयपार्थिवेन्द्रमल्लन पिति–

८. नछोक, थ्वया कत्र्तव्यन श्रीश्रीमहीपतीन्द्रमल्ल बिसेविज्याक, गुणि ओझानं फान कोखाव, स्याम ओझा गंगाधर ओझायां 

   देशत्याग जुव, मेव अनेग कतकनं दुःख सेव, थ्वया कत्र्तव्यनं

 

९. श्रीश्रीजयपार्थिवेन्द्रमल्ल व श्रीश्रीजययोगनरेन्द्रमल्ल व फाव, ओलस थ्व कुपुत्र सियाओ, मूलचूकस सिजलपति ताक, राज्य दुकाय

   मदु धक, थुगुल सियाओ लक्ष्मीनारायणयातं भो–

१०. रोसा बियाओ, श्रीश्रीजयपार्थिवेन्द्रमल्ल फुतकु, चिकुतिया परिवारसहितं फुतुक, श्रीश्रीमहीपतीन्द्रमल्लं फुतकु, थ्व मूलचुकस

    ताङा

    सिजलपति मखयक बोङाओ तओम्ह लक्ष्मीना–

११. रायणं फुतकु, ओलस कुङाओ तओम्ह कंतु मनिरायजुन जगन्नाथजु व मिलय याङओ बिओ, जगन्नाथजु सिस्यलि कंतुन वासर

    नकाओ ओया दाजु दंडपानिन प्रयोग यातका–

१२. ओ मनिरायजु, स्याक, ओलंलि श्रीश्रीजययोगनरेन्द्रमल्ल याकात तयाओ, श्रीश्रीजयभूपालेन्द्रमल्ल फुतके धक सङाओ, स्वम्ह

    राजानं विचाल याङाओ पति चोस्यंतया, थ्वते ग्वम्ह

१३. राजानं ग्वम्हराजाया वंशनं ग्वम्ह काजिनं ग्वम्ह राणीन मेव सुनानं महादेव ओझाया वंश दुकालसा, ओमिसओ खं दयकलसा

    मिपु लंख अन्न दाम वस्त्रादि छुं वस्तु बिलसां श्रीश्रीश्रीत–

१४. लेजु माजुया कुद्दिष्टि राक श्रीश्रीश्रीपशुपति आदिन नेपालस दको देवताया कुदृष्टि लाक जुरो, कोटि पंचमहापातक लाक, कोटि 

    शिवलिङ्गध्वंसन याङा पाप लाक, कोटि अभक्षाभक्ष्य–

१५. न याङा पाप लाक, उपरान्त कोकालसा थ्व सिजलपति सुनानं कोकालसा यिचिल थिचिल यातसां गुप्त यातसां कोकाय धक

    बचन बिलसां कोकायकलसां सम्पूण्र्ण देवताया कुदृष्टि पंच–

१६. महापातक लाको फल जुरो । थ्वते भाखाया दृष्टसाक्षी श्री ३ चन्द्र सूर्य, श्रीश्रीउग्रमल्ल  श्रीश्रीजयभास्करमल्लदेव  ।।

    श्रीविश्वंभर उपाध्या  ।।   श्रीविद्याचन्द्र उपाध्या श्री जयन्त उपाध्या ।।

१७. श्रीकृष्ण भट्ट भाजु ।। श्रीमहेश्वर भट्ट भाजु ।। श्रीहरिशङ्कर भट्ट भाजु ।। नवमीसिंह भाग्वगल भा ।। थ्व चोस्यंतको मानय मयातसा

    थ्व पतिस चोस्यं तको हत्या जुरो ।। सम्वत् ८१८ शुभ ।। 

(Vajrācārya, VS 2056: 305)
स्वस्ती ।। श्री श्री इष्टदेवता प्रीतिन श्री श्री जय योगनरेन्द्र मल्लदेव ठाकुरन थ्व घंठ दुत जुरो ।। सम्वत् ८१६ चैत्र शुक्ल, नवम्यान्तिथौ ।। शुभमस्तु ।।

१. ॐ स्वस्ति ।। श्रीभवान्यै नमः । महारणादृहासिनीं प्रचण्डचंद्रहासिनीं समुण्ड चण्डघातिनीं विहालमुण्डमालिनी । मदान्धदैत्यदारिणीं प्रचण्डरूपधारिणी युगान्तमेघ —

२. न दिनीं नमामि रुद्रकामिनीम् ।। ।। श्रीरत्नमल्लो नृपतिब्र्वभूव त्रिशक्तित ः 

प्राप्तवर प्रसाद : । मात्र्तण्डवेशोऽभवदस्य सूनु:  श्रीसूर्यमल्लो ऽ नलसूर्यतेजा ः तदीयपु—

३.  त्रो ऽ मरमल्लभूपो बभूव भूमीधनदोज्र्जितश्रीः । तदात्मजोऽभूद् भुवि भूरिकीर्तिर्महेन्द्रमल्लो हि महीमहेन्द्र : ।। अभवदतुलतेजास्तत्सुत: सुप्रतापी नृपमणि —

४. शिवसिंहः शत्रुनागेन्द्रसिंह । विसमशरसमश्रीरात्मजस्तस्य राज्ञो भुविहरिहरसिंहो राजते राजसिंहः । अजीजनत्सिद्धिनृसिंहभूपस्तस्मान्नरेन्द्रात्किल 

५. लालमत्यां । श्री कृष्णपादाम्बुरुहैक भृङ्गो महद्यशोमण्डलमण्डिताशः । महोजसा भूसुरसात्कृतश्रिया नृपेण येनाहुतिकोटिसंख्यया विधाय होमं 

६. विधाना महाधिया प्रतिष्ठिता सप्रतिमा रमापतेः राजर्षितोऽस्माद् भुवि भानुमत्यां श्रीश्रीनिवासो नरवासवोऽभूत् । दातृत्वशक्त्याल्पितकल्पबृक्षे, ज्वल

७. त्प्रतापाल्पितसूर्यतेजाः ।। देवेन्द्रो भगभूषितो मनसिजोऽनङागोमृगेन्द्रः पशुः श्रीदःकिंपुरुषेश्वरो जलपतिःपाशी यमःप्रेतराट् राजप्राप्तपराभ—

८. वो दिनमणिशचन्द्रः कलङ्की यतःतुल्यःकोपि निवासभूपिपतिनातेनास्ति नो पिष्टपे । असूत सूनुं वसुधाधिपात्ततो मृगावती पुण्यवती प्रतिव्रता । श्रीयोगमल्लं 

९. वसुधासुधाकरं जीव्याद्वचोभिः स च पूर्वभूभुजां ।। ।। नैपालिकाव्दे रसकुञ्जरा ब्धौ दुर्गापदाम्भोरुहपूजनार्थम् । अचीकरद् गेहमिमं मनोज्ञं स श्रीनिवासश्चतुरस्त्रशोभं ।। तद्गेहाङ्गनमध्येसौ श्रीनिवासो नृवासवः । स्वर्गप्रासाद मकरौत्स रोजकलिकोपमं ।। ।। अतःपरं नेपालभाषया लिख्यते ।। ।।

११. श्रेयोऽस्तु ।। संवत् ७८६ अश्विनशुक्लप्रतिपद्यां तिथौ ।। श्रीसूर्यवंशोदभवरघुकुल तिलक श्रीमणिलाधिपति महाराजधिराज श्रीश्रीजयश्रीनिवासमल्ल 

१२. देवप्रभु ठाकुरसन महानवमी कुन्हु श्री ३ परमेश्वरी पूजायात निमित्तन थ्व मूलचौक दोयका जुरो ।। थ्व मूलचौकया दथुस श्री ३ इष्टदेवता श्रीयन्ताजु—

१३. सके, सुवण्र्णया देवल दोयकं प्रतिष्ठा याङ जुरो ।। ।। पुनभाषा वर्षप्रतिं महानवमीकुन्हु श्री ३ परमेश्वरी पूजायात निमित्तन कुचुमोया जगातया दाम दक्वन

१४. मेस मालक्व दयकं श्री ३ परमेश्वीसके दोहलपे मालकं दुन्ता जुरो ।। भाषा ग्वम्हनमेसस चिन्तायाक जुर, ओम्हन कुचुपोया जगातस चिन्ता यायजुरो ।। शुभ ।।

 

(Sĩha, 2018: XX)

Text:

  1. [svasti sign] oṁ anmaḥ śrī 3 bhīma rāṇeśvarāya || mārgāṇāṃ vighnahaṃtāraṃ pāṇḍavānaṃ

  5. śukravāsare || thva kunhu śrī kṛṣṇamuni vadeju nhavana siṃha prajāpati lakṣa siṃha
  6. prajāpati karrma siṃha prajāpati viṣṇu siṃha prajāpati paṃndu siṃha prajāpa-
  7. ti jogideva prajāpati śivarāma prajāpati siddhirāma prajāpati ku-
  8. tu siṃha prajāpati viṣṇudeva prajāpati dhanadeva prajāpati bhagideva pra-
  9. jāpati ghana prajāpati mānadeva prajāpati thva jimaṅāmha samūha yāṅa-
  10. na śrī 3 bhīma rāṇeśvara prītinaṃ nāyayiti kvahā one phusasa ṣuka-
  11. ola phale dayakaṃ śrī 3 padmapāṇi lokeśvaradeva thva phalesa tasyaṃ
  12. dina jajn͂a yāsyaṃ pratiṣṭhā yāṅā dina juro || che thāy saeva sivdhi
  13. rāma prajāpatina kinimāla lakṣmī mayī putra dhana prajāpati juro
  14. thva phales mata phoyakaṃ siyā phalke phaṃ 2 ra kuḍa 1 śrī 3 buṃ-
  15. gayātanaṃ śrī 3 indrayātanaṃ thvate dānapinte māla juro | thva pha-
  16. lesa sunānaṃ kaciṃgla thaṅāo senakalasā paṃcamahāpātaka rāka
  17. juro || nidāna yaṅāo bhinakalasa uttottara svarggasaṃ prāpta ma-
  18. stu || śubhamastu sarvvadā ||

Translation:

[svasti sign] Salutation to Bhīmarāṇeśvara. The remover of the obstacles on the road [when travelling for a business], the jewel of the head ornaments of Pāṇḍava [clan]. Salutation to the destroyer of Kaurava [clan] and who is the beloved of Draupadi. Holding a mace and who is giant in the figure, who cuts the enemy into pieces. I salute to him who has the strength equal to hundreds of Navanāgas.

May all be well. Dated Samvat 871 (NS or 1750 CE), on the 13th day of bright half of the Lunar month of Mangsira, on Friday. On this day, after making a group of 15 person led by Kṛṣṇamuni Vadeju (Shakya) including Nhavana Siṃha Prajāpati, Lakṣa Siṃha Prajāpati, Karrma Siṃha Prajāpati, Viṣṇu Siṃha Prajāpati, Paṃdu Siṃha Prajāpati, Jogideva Prajāpati, Śivarāma Prajāpati, Siddhirāma prajāpati, Kutu Siṃha Prajāpati, Viṣṇudeva Prajāpati, Dhanadeva Prajāpati, Bhagideva Prajāpati, Ghana Prajāpati, Mānadeva Prajāpati, a six bayed phalcā on the way to go down to Nāyahiṭi has been built in the devotion to thrice venerable Bhīmarāṇeśvara and established (the icon of) thrice venerable Padmapāṇi Lokeśvara (in the phalcā). Rām Prajāpati, his wife Kinimāla Lakṣmī Mayi and son Dhana Prajapati of the same place are the responsible persons of the phalcā. On the days of the [chariot] festivals of thrice venerable Buṃgama Lokeśvara and Indrajātra, burning wick lamp and 2 pāthis of puffed rice and meat shall be offered in the phalcā. If anybody (tries to) destroy the phalcā creating quarrels, s/he shall get the 5 kinds of great sins. If repairs and solves the problems, s/he shall get continuous prosperity [in this life] and [after the life] may get an abode in heaven. May all be well.

The inscription of the phalcā outside Jyābahal Bahil of Patan

  1. Om swasti śreyo˜stu || Samvat 788 Vaiśāṣa śu-
  2. kla tṛtīyāyāṃ tithau, kṛttikā pra rohini
  3. Nakṣatre sobhāgeyoge Śaniścaravāsare ||
  4. Jyāthabāhāra vihāri vaṃtāripi(bi??)che | Nani
  5. Vaṃtāgṛha || Harirāma Mā(Bhā??)vosana thwatā-
  6. nāmana tiri Dhavaṃti ubhayasta nāmana thaw
  7. Phare dra(da)yekā Śrī 3 Rokyaśvara saktisahi-
  8. tana thwa pharesa thāpanā yaña dina ju-
  9. ro || Thwa pharesa, Indrajātrā Svānachā kunhu
  10. Śrī Rokeśvara Tārā pujā yāñana dānapite
  11. Thute pra 1 chekna, mata choyake pha 2 siyāphake ñe
  12. 1 jipa thaw kuḍa 1 rā pāru, mvāta, sanhāna, pāta 2 dha
  13. Ri kuḍa 1 baji kuḍa 1 kaguri thute dayakemāra
  14. Thute cintā yāka gvahasti Gunasiṃha Bhāvo, Saṃ-
  15. du Rāma Bhāvo, Datharāche Madhu Bhāvo jajamāna pu-

  17. Cintā yāyamāra ropayā kāre pañcamā-
  18. hāpātaka rāka juro ||
historical event transliteration and tra:
Interpretation of the inscription:
On Saturday, the third day of the bright lunar fortnight of Vaiśākha in the year 788 (1668 AD), the construction of this phalcā and installation of the image of Lokeśvara with his Śakti in the phalcā sponsored by Harirāma Bhāvo and his wife Dhavaṃti of the nani to the east of Jyāthabāhāra Vihāra was completed. Here, the nani to the east of the Jyāthabāhāra Vihāra or Jyābahāḥbahī is Lũchẽ Nani itself. Hence, it is evident that a person named Harirāma and his wife Dhavaṃti from Jyāpu community of Lũchẽ Nani had sponsored the construction of the phalcā and installation of an image of Lokeśvara with Śakti or his female consort. He also established a guthi for hosting a puja of Lokeśvara and Tārā on the day of Svāṃchā during Indra Jātrā. The inscription also clearly mentions the names of four persons, all from the Jyāpu community, who were to take care of the guthi without any greed. Those who become greedy will have to bear the pañcamahāpāpa. (Rajendra Shakya, 2016)

The inscription of the caitya in front of the phalcā

  1. Om Namo Buddhāya Namo Dharmmāya Namo Śaṃghāyaṃ || Taṃ Bauddhadevamagalaprameṃsa-
  2. rvvamūrti Bramhendra Viṣṇuśaśiśekhara rūpanisthaṃ heraṃvasūyaryavidhu-
  3. śaktidhara swarūpaṃ caitraṃ namāmi satataṃ śubhadraṃ narāṇā|| Śre˜stu-
  4. Samvat, 800 Kārtikamāse kṛṣṇapakṣe pañcamyāyāṃ tithau poṣyanakṣatre
  5. Śuklayogya Budhabāsare, thwa kunhu Śrīcākhābāhāra cākalaṃ yatā Śrī-
  6. Jyāthabāhāra Bahirinhawane Śrī 3 caitabāhāra dayakava ahorātra
  7. Jña yāñāwa pratiṣṭā yāñā dina juro || Thwa thāyaṣavaśvaka phare
  8. Jirṇṇauddhāra yāñāva Śrī 3 Umāmaheśvara sthāpanā yāñā juro || Thwa
  9. Verasa Nepāreśvara Śrīmaṇiglādhipati Śrī Śrī Jaya Śrīnivāsa Malla De-
  10. va prabhu ṭhākulasa vijayarājye verasa pramāna Bhagīratha Bhaiyā Bhāro-
  11. sa paprajyāyavela juro tha verasa Cokhā Bāhārayā cākara yetāche-
  12. ya Harinandana Duvāra Bhārosana thuva iṣṭadevatā prītina duntā
  13. Bāhāra rivi burova 1 ja 3 gvārakhwāta buro 1 java 1 bhūya vinatamayina
  14. Duntā hasajola vatika karpa chi 1 java 2 thwate buyā varasānana prarṣa-
  15. yati katini bunhiśi kunhu sakhvārana pasya cākamata choyake pvāta
  16. 16 pharesa pvāta 3 pīthiganansa pvāta 2 pharesa dānapitemāra sati ku-
  17. nhu homa choyake cahra chāyamāra, gurubāhāraju mātrājupani mhaṃ 5
  18. Mopaskebhara, Kārtika kṛṣṇa pañcami kunhu devapujā yāyamāra thvaṃ
  19. Devapujāyā Ñākhācokayā Ratna Karaju yāta thwaguthina vā phaṃ
  20. 27 biyamāra juro prasekhaṃ selhoyāta renake vā phaṃ 7 bhāra thvagate-
  21. ya citā yāka Jyāthabāhāra Viṣṇu Śrīdharamuniju Śrī Devajoti-
  22. ju Śrīsupuridevaju thwate bhākhā cosyaṃ tako mayātasā pañca-
  23. mahāpātaka lāka lobha mayākale uttottara juro śuva ||

Interpretation of the inscription in brief:
On Wednesday, the fifth day of the dark lunar fortnight of Kārtik in the year NS 800 (1680 AD), a caitya was consecrated with a fire offering in front of Jyābahāḥbahī, which is to the south of the premise of Cākhā Vihār. The renovation of the phalcā at this place was also carried out, along with the installation of the image of Umāmaheśvara. The event took place during the reign of King Śrīnivāsa Malla, while Bhagīratha Bhaiyā's influence was growing (??). Harinandan Duvāra Bhāro from the southern section of Cokhā (Cākhā) Vihār had also donated property in the name of his Īṣṭa Devatā. The inscription hints at the existence of another vihār in the vicinity by the name Cākhābāhāra. This vihār, which probably gave the now-widely-popular name Cābahāl to the area, was situated to the north of Jyābahāḥbahī.

  1. oṃ namaḥ nārāyaṇaṃ namaskṛtyaṃ naraṃ cau(cai)va narottamāṃ(mam) devīṃ saraś(s)vatīṃ (vyāsaṃ) ta-

    tithau
  3. bṛhaspativāsare thva kunhu kutubāhālayā laghuvaṃśa rāutta  si _ _
  4. ... ... sa_ siddhilakṣmimaī thva nimha stri pu[ru]khasena svapurta divaṃgata _ _
  5. datta bābusa māmana calaṣu lāṃche͂sa phale dayakaṃ śrī nārāyaṇa mūrtti _
  6. _ _ _ pratiṣṭhā yāsyaṃ śrī 3 candamāsasa duntā pākubuṃ rova 3 java 3
  7. _tasiṃdhuṣacābuṃ rova 3 puna dhalasikva karṣa 7 thvate buṃyā _ _ syanana
  8. _ phalesa mata choyakaṃ dāna biyamāla buṃgayātāna enātava || ni... ...
  9. _ _bhāropanisena yāyamāla saeva vaiśāṣa lachiṃ śrī 3 buṃga yāta ... ...
  10. ... ... || śrī _ _ 2 vaṃ _ _ tya japa pāṭha rācake || śrī 3 bo _ śvara ... ...
  11.  ... ... kārttika lachiṃ mata biyake māla ... ...
  12. ... ... varṣaprati ... ...
  13. ... ... yāyamāla  cosye tako yātasā utrottara juya || cosya (tako)
  14. mayātasā paṃcamāhāpāpa lāka || śubhamastu ||

 

Translation of the inscription:

(The beginning part of the inscription is the praises of Lord Narayan)

In [NS] 895 (1775 CE), on the 6th day of dark half of Lunar month of Māgha, Thrusday. On this day, the couple from Kutu Bāhā, Si... ... Raghuvaṃśa Rāutta and his wife Siddhilakṣīmayī. The mother of the dead son has constructed this phalcā of Calkhu, Lāṃche͂ establishing in it an icon of Śrīnārāyaṇa in the name of the dead son ... Datta Bābu.

Three ropani and 3 yava land of Pākubuṃ, 3 ropanis of land of Tasiṃ Dhuṣacābuṃ and 7 karṣa of land of Dholosikvaṃ are offered.  Those lands shall be used to repair the phalcā when destroyed. Burning lamps shall be offered there during the festival of red Matsyendranātha.... The Bhāro (noble) brothers shall do this during the whole month of Vaiśakha during the festival of red Matsyendranātha .... [Also,] japa (recitation of mantra) and pāṭha (recitation of sacred texts) shall also be performed.... A lamp shall be offered in the whole month of Kārtika.... Every year.... If done according to what has been written, he shall get prosperous and if not done he shall get five great sins .... May all be well.

२. न परि त्यहाका बासिन्दालाई र त्यसै गाउँको बाटो गरि आर्उने जाने प्रजा प्राणिलाई स्मेट

५. का  हजुरमा जाहेर भएकोले सो गाउँमा कलधारा राखिबक्सने ईच्छा प्रकट गरि सो का-

७. सुरु हुन नपार्उदै उँहाको स्वर्गारोहण भएकाले र्उहाका पार्उको हरबखत्त् भक्ति गरि र-

९. हु पृथुलाधीश श्री श्री श्री महाराज जुद्धसम्सेर जङ्ग बहादुर राणा प्राईम्मिनिष्टर 
१०. एण्ड सुप्रीम कम्याण्डर ईन चीफबाट कलधारा तयार गराई प्रविष्टा स्मेट्र गरी 

  • ११. भुयो भुयो भाबिनो भुमि पालान्नत्वानत्वायाचत्रेरामचन्द्र ।।

१३. भन्ने यो पुरानो श्लोकलाई दोहर्यार्उदै पछि हुने सज्जनहरुसंग प्रार्थना गरी स्वर्ग बा-

  1. [Svasti sign] śrī bhīmasenāya namaḥ || mārggāṇāṃ vighnahantāraṃ dāṇuvāraṃ siromaṇi || Kauravāḥ māra saṃhārā-
  2. rtamvande draupadipriyaṃ || svasti || samvatsara 871 phālguṇa māse śukla pakṣe || tṛtīyāyāṃntithau
  3. utatra bhādra pra revatī nakṣetre || śubha varaśika yoge tetilagaraṇe | yathā mūharttake || ādi-
  4. tavāsare || kumbha rāśigate savitari|| mīnarāśigate candramasi || tasmindine śrī matchri śrībhīmase-
  5. na pritina nhapā dasya cogva phale jīrṇa juyāva coṅasa bauddhagītakṛta dhamma dyakā guru thāpanā dhuṅā _ _
  6. kula bhāro, lakṣmīsiṃha bhāvo, kajhita khapiṃche nāyhiti phusa gṛha prajāpati gyānasiṃha prajāpati bhā-
  7. gīrathasiṃ bhāvo sisiṃha prajāpati sūryyasiṃha prajāpati mukundasiṃha prajāpati dhantasiṃha prajā-
  8. pati bidhusiṃha prajāpati anantasiṃha prajāpati dhanaśaṃkara prajāpati puna dharmasiṃha prajāpa-

(On top of the inscription is a small statue of Lord Buddha)

 

Provisional Translation:

Salutations to the venerable Bhīmasena, remover of obstacles, the jewel of head (ornament). Salutations to him who killed the Kauravas and who is Draupadī's beloved one. May all be well. In the year of (NS) 871 (1759 CE), on the third day of bright fortnight of Phālguna, on the constellation of Uttara Bhādra and Revati, subha-yoga, Teliya Karaṇa, Sunday when the sun is in Aquarius and the moon in Pisces.

On this day, the decayed rest house which was built in devotion to Bhīmasen was renovated as a sataḥ by the group of Kula Bhāro, Lakṣmīsiṃha Bhāro, Gyānasiṃha Prajāpati who is the senior member lives near Khapinche, Nayhiti, Prajāpati Bhāgīrathasiṃ Bhāvo, Sisiṃha Prajāpati, Sūryyasiṃha Prajāpati, Mukundasiṃha Prajāpati, Dhantasiṃha Prajāpati, Bidhusiṃha Prajāpati, Anantasiṃha Prajāpati, Dhanaśaṃkara Prajāpati, Dharmasiṃha Prajāpati, Masiṃ Prajāpati, Dhamarā Prajāpati, Aṣchi Prajāpati, Sūryyalakṣmīmayi who is the wife of senior member after establishing the Caryā Guṭhī and a guru (in it). Again, the same group of 17 persons led by Gyānasiṃha Prajāpati offers 68 mohor coins to worship the deities of the phalcā by making a dāna of burning wick lamp with four mānās of oil during the festivals of Indrajātrā and Rāto (red) Matsyendranātha Lagana-jātrā after offering 1 pāthī (?), puffed rice 2 pāthī, 12 daṃ of rice beer and one type of meat. For both, the same amount (of offering) shall be made.

The responsible persons are the same group of 17 persons led by Gyānasiṃha Prajāpati. Again, it is not allowed to give shelter to a jogī (Kapālī), dopa (do͂) and phogiṃ (begger) in the phale. If allowed by anybody, he shall get five kinds of great sin (killing a woman, brahman, cow etc.) and shall bear the anger of the three times venerable Bhīmasen. May all be well.

This (Phalcā) Rest house is built in NS 903 (1783 CE). On full moon day of March, the butter lamps are to be lit and distribute beaten rice, soya beans, meat, and rice in this phalcā.
The construction of this phalcā was made possible by the donations of Dhanta Bhāva, Dhanju Bhāva, Dhanesśvara Bhāva, Dhanmān Bhāva, Birvanta Bhāava and Bhagijani Maĩ.
A piece of land (one and half ropani= 760 sq.m approx.) is donated to renovate the phalcā.
In case of any problem guthiyār Sundaha Bhāva, Palidev Bhāva and Dhanta Bhāva will decide , solve the problem and organize a feast.
Śuva

Roman transliteration of Tashi Gomang Inscription

1. ? svasti śrī 3 magalacete,,yā jaṃta śrīśrī maṃjuvajrācāryā,,vatāra,, tāmrakāra gvatasya utpanna:

2. dhamasiṃ(.)se putra harṣaratna thao babuyā nāmana dutā lipa(ta)sa śunāna thva jaṃta thva thāsana ghatibahri yā:

3. ya mā(lasā) thothyaṃ tayamāla,, sāchi śrī māhākāla hāratigana jula śu(nā)naṃ ghatibahri yātasā śrīyā kudisti hnāpayā:

4. thyaṃ tamyaśīyā śudisti,, phala prāpati śubha saṃvat 995 mti jesta kṛṣṇa 10 roja 2 śubhaṃ ll

 

Translation by Kashinath Tamot:

[Siddhi symbol] (May it be) auspicious! The Yantra of Thrice Blessed Mangalacaitya has been established in the name of own’s father by Harsha Ratna, the son of Dharmasimha (inscr. Dhamasim...), who was descended from the clan of Tamrakar (and) who is the incarnation of Manjuvajra Acarya. Later, if anybody has to make change (“ghatibarhi”, lit. small-big/less-more) in this place, it should be kept like this. Witnesses are Blessed Mahakal (and) the family of Harati. If anyone makes different (“ghatibarhi”), he will be viewed with evil eyes by Blessed ones (Mahakal and Harati). One who builds it as previous (donor), he will be viewed with good eyes, he will get fruit (of it). (It was established in) the Good Era (Nepal Samvat) dated 995 Jyestha, waning moon 10, weekday 2 (Monday) (28 June, 1875). (Let it be) good!

inscription from NS 567

This stone inscription by King Vasanta Deva (r. 506-532) lies in the northwest corner of temple plinth (# 3 in the floor plan). For the first time it was published in the ‘Abhilekha Saṃgraha, part- 5’ by Itihāsa Saṃśodhana Maṇḍala and afterwards published by  Vajracharya (VS 2030,112). According to Dhanavajra Vajracharya, the upper part of the inscription was damaged and more than half of the part was buried.

Text: (only the concerning portion from the stone inscription - provided by Nutan Sharma)

  1. oṁ namaḥ śrīraktalokeśvarāya || namaskārāyāṃ || śrīganeśvā[rā]yanamaḥ ||

.... .... .....

9. _ _ _ || svasti || śrīnepālamaṇḍale lalitāpurīmahānagagyktarvartti cyāsala tola saptapurīmahāvihāravirājita śrī 3 śakyamuni buddha śā-

10. sana brahmacaryabhikṣu śrī maṇiratna vaidya bhāryyā indralakṣmī thvate strī puruṣayā dharmmacitta utpatti yaṅā

11. sthānadhipati śrī 3 ganeśayā devālaya jīrṇoddhāra yāṅa ganeśa mūrtti suvarṇayā dayakāva punaḥ maṃgalabā-

12. ra śevā ṣalaka sammata yāṅa suvarṇa lepita gajuri dayakāva saṃvata 982 jyeṣṭha vadi 4 sa pratiṣṭhā yāṅā-

13. va divaṃgata juyāva vanapiṃ putra putrī pautra pautrī sukhāvatī vāsa lāyamāla dhakaṃ bhāvanā yāṅa prati-

14. varṣa indrajātrā kunhu deva pūjā yāṅa dāna biya dharmmaśārāsa bhajana yāka panitaṃ naivedya

15. taya thva dharmmaśālā jirṇoddhāra yāya thvateka karmma yāyata dānapati brahmacaryya-

16. bhiṣu śrī m aṇiratnajuna saṃvat 983 bhādra śudi 13 thva kunhu thache-

17. ṣelakṣetranāma bu lova 5 duntā julo bhāṣā thvate buyā āśyana thvate

18. karma yāṅāva paraśeṣa dakva dāna patiyā saṃtānana bhuktalapā du jula

19. thvate puṇyana dānapatiyā ihalokasa dharmma artha kāmanādi āyu

20. jaśa prasaṃ sukha ārogya dhana saṃtāna lādhda juyāva pratra sukhā-

21. vativāsa prāpti juya māla || maṇiratna indralakṣmī || śubhamastu sarvaṣāṃ ||

22. _ dā malanaliṃ rājadatta munithakuṃ || hirālakṣmī lānimunī cijamatī ratnakumārī

 

Provisional Translation:

  1. Salutation to venerable Rakta (red) Lokeśvara. Namaskār. Salutation to venerable Ganeśa.

9-22.  Bhikṣu Maṇiratna Vaidya and his wife Indralakṣmī, husband and wife who live in Nepal Maṇḍala in Lalitpur Mahānagara at Cyāsala Tole in Saptapuri Mahāvihāra, after originating dharmacitta (religious feeling) they have renovated this shrine of thrice venerable Ganeśa, Lord of the area, [and also] after making a golden icon of Ganeśa [and] also organizing Mangalbār Seva khalak (Tuesday Service Group of Gaṇeśa) [and] making a gold plated pinnacle, they have established [all of them in the temple] on the 4th day of the dark half of the Lunar month of Jeṣṭha in [NS] 982 (1862 CE).  And, wishing their dead son, daughter, grandson [and] granddaughters may get an abode in Sukhāvati heaven. [They] have arranged naivedya (food) to worship the deity and bhajan (recitation of the religious songs) every year on Indrajātrā in the dharmaśāla which was donated by them. In order to renovate the dharmaśālā, the donor Bhikṣu Maṇiratna has offered 5 ropanis of land named Thacheṣelaṣetra on 13th day of bright half of the lunar month of Bhadra in [NS] 983 (1863 CE). After performing such activities, the descendants of the donor may consume rest of the income (of the land). From this virtue, the donors may get dharma, fulfillment of their desires, prosperity, long life, fame, pleasure, health, money and children in this life and after this life (after their death) they may get to abode in Sukhavati, heaven. Maniratna, Indralakṣmī. May all be well. _ dā Malanasiṃ Rāj Datta, Munithakuṃ, Hiralakṣmī, Lānimunī, Cijamatī, Ratnakumārī (other family members).

Translation:

In the dark half of the month of Caitra, in NS 785 (1665 CE), Jake Bhāvo as a head and including other members named Atarāja Bhavo, Hākadeva Bhavo, Śugusi ˜ha Bhavo, Luterāma Bhavo, Jasarāma , Bhavo………………………………….Jagarāma Bhavo have constructed the phalcā with three bays. It is built facing east in Pithachẽ Lāchi area. The norm (rule) of worshipping Buṅgadyaḥ on the day of every full moon is established (Purṇimā sevā). If anyone tries to destroy the phalcā, he/she will have to bear Pañca Mahā Pāpa (Five worst sins) where as a good-doer of it will be rewarded with happiness and prosperity. May all be well.

[Svasti sign] Salutation to venerable Lakṣmīnārāyaṇa 3 (times). On the 14th day of bright half of the Lunar month of Vaiśākha in auspicious saṃvat dated (NS) 832, Bhāgīrāma Bhāro from Yatāchẽ has built this phalcā in the name of his dead father Candrarāmā Bhāro and offered land for the guthi. From that land burn 3 oil wick lamp and offer food every year on the Nhugalyāta (jātrā) of Matsyendranatha and Dvādasi jātrā (of Indrajātrā).... May all be well.

historical event transliteration and tra:
Constructed with the collective donation by the Bhāvos of the area, the construction (expansion of the Phalcā into five bays) was completed on Thursday, the 8th day of the bright lunar fortnight of Bhādra in NS 832 (1712 CE). Later, an image of Amoghapāśa Lokeśvara was consecrated on Tuesday, the 6th day of the bright lunar fortnight of Jeṣṭha of NS 833 (1713 AD).

नेसं ८३२ भाद्र शुक्ल अष्टमी, बिहिबार खुनु स्थानिय भावो समुदायं थुगु फल्चा दय्‌के (फल्चायात त:धंका: न्याकव:या दय्‌के) क्वचा:गु जुल । लिपा नेसं ८३३ जेष्ठ शुक्ल षष्ठी, मंगलबार खुनु अमोघपाश लोकेश्वरया मूर्ती पलिस्था या:गु जुल ।

historical event references source:
Inscription of NS 788 (1668 CE)

 

On Tuesday,[1] 6th day of the bright fortnight of Jyeṣṭha NS 833, Statue of Amoghapāśa Lokeśvara has been erected in the Phalcā. On Wednesday, 8th day of the bright fortnight of Bhādra NS 832, Ranhasiṃha Bhāvo, Parusiṃha Bhāvo, Lvayarāma Bhāvo, his son Ratnaki Rāma Bhāvo, Lakṣmīrāma Bhāvo, Dhanaṃsiṃha Bhāvo, Viśvarāma Bhāvo all from Jyābāhā Bahī ṭola made a Phalcā and established a guṭhī donating 1 karṣa (1/4 ropanī) land for its management. With the income of the land every year on the 14th day of the bright fortnight of Bhādra, 1 pāthī beaten rice with 2 prastha meat, 1 kuḍa soaked pea and 1 prastha soybean should be distributed sitting in the Phalcā.

 

 

 

[1] The date is unclear
historical event transliteration and tra:
Dedicated to Rokyaśvara and Śaktī, Harirāma Bhāvo and his wife Dhavaṃti of the Lũchẽ Nani sponsored the construction of the phalcā to the east of Jyāthabāhāra Vihāra, completed on Saturday, the third day of the bright lunar fortnight of Vaiśākha in NS 788 (1668 CE).

नेसं ७८८ वैशाख शुक्ल तृतिया, सञ्चरबार खुनु हरिराम भावो व वय्‌क:या तिरि धवंन्तिं ज्याथबाहार विहारया पूर्वय् थुगु फल्चा दय्‌का: शक्ति सहितया लोकेश्वर छम्ह नं पलिस्था या:गु जुल ।
